 popularity to the thousands of WordPress plug-ins that are available online. These plug-ins are programming codes that enhance the functionality of your site or blog, without modifying the core code of your site. With thousands of open source plug-ins available, a website owner can easily get any functionality that he might need to enhance his website. Since most of these plug-ins are free, they also help website owners to keep their expenses at a minimum.</p>\n<p>But every advancement in technology is accompanied by some risks. Most of these plug-ins are developed by individuals or teams of developers with the sole aim of implementing a specific functionality. However, there also is a certain breed of people who are making plug-ins that are designed to access your information confidentiality and integrity and pose various types of security risks. A hacker can create a plug-in that can infect your website with <a title="What is malware" href="http://www.websitedefender.com/what-is-malware/">malware</a> and you may not even notice that your site has been infected. Since most web users do not have significant knowledge about web programming languages, it is difficult to know which plug-ins are safe to install and which ones can impact WordPress security and entail potential risks for your site.</p>\n<p>According to a study published in NetworkWorld in 2009, more than 640,000 websites and 5.8 million web pages are infected with malware. The <a title="Avoid Google Blacklist " href="http://www.websitedefender.com/web-security/seo-poisoning/avoid-google-blacklist/">Google blacklist</a> of malware infected sites has doubled from the previous year. Although these statistics are worrying, there is a way to identify website vulnerabilities (plug-ins, malwares, hacker activities, etc) without needing technical knowhow.</p>\n<h3><strong>Secure Your Website With WebsiteDefender</strong></h3>\n<p>The advantages you stand to gain by using WebsiteDefender to monitor your website are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong> WordPress <strong>Security checks</strong></strong>: WebsiteDefender offers specific checks to ensure <a title="WordPress security plugin by WebsiteDefender" href="http://www.websitedefender.com/websitedefender-wordpress-security-plugin/">WordPress security</a> (WP). It not only checks whether the plug-ins installed on your site are safe, it also ensures that your database is protected and your WP installation is secure.</li>\n<li><strong>Protects your website from malware and/or hacking activity</strong>: WebsiteDefender checks your website for any threats from malware or security access, and notifies you when it detects any breach or security violation. It also checks whether your site is blacklisted by any search engine.</li>\n<li><strong>File change notifications</strong>: WebsiteDefender monitors the files on your website and tracks any changes made to them. It highlights these changes and presents them to the website owner in the most user friendly manner.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>WebsiteDefender is a complete package that ensures the safe and secure working of your website or blog, and prevents it from any suspicious or harmful activity. One of the biggest advantages of WebsiteDefender is that it requires no maintenance and no installation or technical proficiency to operate.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:86:"http://www.websitedefender.com/web-security/eliminating-wordpress-security-risks/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:62:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			