:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"website security";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:38:"http://www.websitedefender.com/?p=4443";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:362:"Website security is like physical security. From barricades and building surveillance in the physical realm to software updates and audit logging in the digital world, there are tons of variables involved. Either way, one oversight – one slip-up – can be costly. For website security, there’s hardly any area that’s more impactful than user account [...]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Adriana Bantu";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3284:"<p><img class="alignleft  wp-image-4448" title="Account credential security checks from WebsiteDefender" src="http://www.websitedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/security-check1-300x225.jpg" alt="Security checks for account credentials from WebsiteDefender" width="270" height="203" />Website security is like physical security. From barricades and building surveillance in the physical realm to software updates and audit logging in the digital world, there are tons of variables involved. Either way, one oversight – one slip-up – can be costly.</p>\n<p>For <a title="WebsiteDefender Website Security" href="http://www.websitedefender.com/">website security</a>, there’s hardly any area that’s more impactful than user account and access control. Abuse of account credentials is a common and easily-exploited security flaw that doesn’t get nearly the attention it deserves. With WebsiteDefender you can keep tabs on user accounts and be alerted when something changes or needs attention.</p>\n<p>Here’s how you can benefit from WebsiteDefender’s account-related security checks:<br />\n• <strong>Creation of new administrator accounts</strong><br />\nA sign of a compromised website is the creation of accounts that don’t belong – especially accounts with administrator privileges.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Modification of administrator or user account credentials</strong><br />\nIf an attacker compromises your administrator account, he may attempt to change its settings to cover his tracks or even lock you out. As with administrator credentials, user account credentials being adjusted could be a tip off that something’s going on.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Modification of administrator or user account email addresses</strong><br />\nIf a criminal hacker gains access to a website account , he may attempt to redirect any requests to himself. If this happened you may be none the wiser until after the damage has been done.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Weak account credentials</strong><br />\nMissing or weak <a title="Web Passwords" href="http://www.websitedefender.com/web-security/web-passwords-are-the-weakest-link/">web passwords</a> are arguably the greatest Web security flaw, yet this problem is widespread. Even if your account may have strong passphrase but there could be other accounts that are putting your website at risk. It’s good to know where things stand in advance.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Weak database credentials (MySQL)</strong><br />\nIt’s one thing to have weak credentials for your website front-end. But having them on your database server opens up an entirely new set of issues. Understanding how your database may be at risk is critical so this check is a must.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Root account used for database access (MySQL)</strong><br />\nA well-secured database environment doesn’t use the Linux ‘root’ account for database access. Any such usage could be an indicator that your root account has been compromised and action may be needed.</p>\n<p>WebsiteDefender can look at your website configuration and flag any known or potential flaws related to user accounts. This information is invaluable for maintaining a <a title="The importance of a secure website" href="http://www.websitedefender.com/secure-website/">secure website</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:100:"http://www.websitedefender.com/web-security/websitedefender-account-credentials-security-check/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:65:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"The WebsiteDefender Multi-Site Edition Approaching Official Release";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:130:"http://www.websitedefender.com/announcements/websitedefender-news/websitedefender-multi-site-edition-approaching-official-release/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:139:"http://www.websitedefender.com/announcements/websitedefender-news/websitedefender-multi-site-edition-approaching-official-release/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0: